plays_per_point â€“ How many offensive plays a team runs for each point scored. Lower values indicate efficient scoring with fewer plays per drive.

quarter_var â€“ The variability in points scored per quarter. High variance can suggest inconsistency or momentum swings; low variance may indicate steady performance.

yards_per_play â€“ Average yards gained per offensive play. A core measure of how productive a team is when they run or pass the ball.

yards_per_point â€“ How many total yards a team needs to generate one point. Lower numbers signal that the team is turning yards into points effectively (good red zone/finish rate).

late_lift â€“ The difference in points scored in the second half vs.Â the first half. Positive values suggest strong finishes or comeback potential; negative values may reveal fading late in games.

identity_week1 <- tibble(
  week = 1,
  team = c("Washington", "SW Kansas", "Oregon"),
  plays_per_point = c(46/33, 39/63, 44/36),
  quarter_var = c(13, 14, 12),
  yards_per_play = c(206/46,200/39,274/44),
  yards_per_point = c(206/33,200/63,274/36),
  late_lift = c(7, -13, -12)
)

identity_week2 <- tibble(
  week = 2,
  team = c("Washington", "SW Kansas", "Oregon"),
  plays_per_point = c(33/35, 45/20, 45/28),
  quarter_var = c(29,7,14),
  yards_per_play = c(100/33,242/45,266/45),
  yards_per_point = c(100/33,242/20,266/28),
  late_lift = c(35,6,-16)
)

long_identity_df <- bind_rows(identity_week1, identity_week2)

long_identity_df %>%

ðŸ§­ Identity Radar â€“ Week Comparison

radar_week1 <- identity_week1 %>%
  pivot_longer(-c(week, team), names_to = "metric", values_to = "value")

radar_week2 <- identity_week2 %>%
  pivot_longer(-c(week, team), names_to = "metric", values_to = "value")

radar_all <- bind_rows(radar_week1, radar_week2)

# Overlayed radar chart
ggplot(radar_all, aes(x = metric, y = value, group = interaction(team, week), color = team, linetype = as.factor(week))) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  coord_polar() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Radar Chart: Team Identity Comparison (Weeks 1 & 2)",
       subtitle = "Solid = Week 1, Dashed = Week 2",
       x = NULL, y = NULL)

ðŸ“‰ Delta Table: Week-over-Week Change

delta_df <- identity_week2 %>%
  select(-week) %>%
  left_join(identity_week1 %>% select(-week), by = "team", suffix = c("_w2", "_w1")) %>%
  mutate(across(ends_with("_w1") & !starts_with("team"), ~ get(sub("_w1", "_w2", cur_column())) - ., .names = "delta_{.col}")) %>%
  select(team, starts_with("delta")) %>%
  mutate(across(-team, round, 2))
